title: For Sale:  Remington 870 Marine Magnum
postcontent:
I have up for sale, a Rem 870 Marine Magnum. It has the 18.5" bead sight 12G barrel for 2.75" and 3". It has a +2 extension on it like the Tactical models. I added a Choate Mark V Pistol Grip Stock to it and a 5 round side saddle onto the side of the stock (which is affixed with 6 screws and can be removed).
It runs pretty darn smooth and has no blemishes on it. Much smoother than a new Express. The barrel is in awesome condition. This weapon is nickel plated inside and out for the ultimate in corrosion protection. This includes bolt, sling studs, mag tube extension, bead sight, mag tube clamp, etc. It makes a great truck gun or JIC gun. To my eyes, it seems to have a plastic trigger housing (like the Express models) with a different coating on it and I think the standard springs but seems to have the machined extractor. I have a Tactical model to compare to and the Tac has the mold seams and the little dot imprint on the extractor whereas the Marine Magnum has grinding/machining grooves on most of the sides of the extractor like it was cut from a block of steel. I have the original stock as well. Front grip (which is an express) was machined and chamfered to not overlap the receiver for side saddle install on the receiver itself. I had a TacStar 6 round saddle on it for a while so I know those fit. Boyt case, MOLLE pouch, radios and feet not included.
My price is shipped from me to your FFL in CONUS except CT, NY, CA or MA or otherwise illegal to purchase. If I need to go to an FFL on my side, the cost is not included. No PayPal please. Photos are in a photobucket album if you want more images.
I am thinning the pump gun herd, but I'd be interested in some potential parts for hunting 870 stuff (chokes, rifled bbl, etc.) or towards an 1100 Tac-4 or 12G Auto-5 to play with and the like. Ammo is always good; 4~6 shot, buck anything, slugs, etc.

title: For Sale:  Custom Heckler & Koch USP 45 Full-size Compensated
postcontent: Re-listing due to a flakey out of town buyer.This German made brute is an absolute BEAST! These highly sought after pistols have been a mainstay of the Special Operations community for years for the simple reason that HK works, and works well. This one is the prefered variant #1, meaning that the slide lever acts as a de-cocker and a safety. You can carry this "cocked & locked" in 1911 fashion, or uncocked as a double action. This gun is outfitted with a 6" stainless steel National Match Grade, Compensated (cuts in the exposed end of barrel that allows excess gas to vent upwards during fire, reducing muzzle rise) barrel, that mitigates muzzle rise down to next to nothing. It has a HK competition recoil spring, making the racking of the slide feel like hot butter on teflon. It is easier to rack than EVERY 9mm I own. One of the most significant features of the USP is the mechanical recoil reduction system. This system is incorporated into the recoil spring assembly, and consists of a captive coil spring around the guide rod. This feature, combined with the compensated barrel, make this gun feel more like a 40 S&W, even with 45 +P loads. It has the HK short reset combat trigger, that allows for a higher cyclic rate, without being dangerously light like a competition trigger. Included with the gun are 3) 12 round factory, and 1) 22 round aftermarket magazines, a black leather pancake style belt holster. She has HK installed night sights, that are dimming, but still work like a charm. The frame rails, exterior of the chamber and feed ramps have all been polished to a mirror shine. This was my personal sidearm on a security detail in N. Africa, and she served me well, not once giving me a click when I asked for a bang (regardless of ammo), always supremely accurate and manageable. She has some minor scratches on the proprietary "Hostile Environment" nitride finish, but nothing down to the bare metal. There is also some minor scuffing at the heel of the grip. Overall, I'd put the finish in the 80-85% category. The bore is bright and shiney, with great rifling, and the gun functions flawlessly. This isn't a civilian toy, but rather a professional's tool.

title: For Trade:  Milled Bulgarian Arsenal SLR-95 AK47 1850 rounds & 11 mags
postcontent:
Up for sale/trade I have a Bulgarian Arsenal Milled SLR-95 with 11 mags (10 steel & 1 polymer), and 1850 rounds of ammo.

Seems like every AK add I see claims to be "the best" AK ever made, but talk is cheap. The SLR-95 actually is the most rare, & highly sought after AK47 ever produced. Here's the history;
The SLR-95 was made in the original ARSENAL factory in Bulgaria. This factory is world renouned for producing the highest quality AKs ever produced. The 95 has a milled reciever, milled fire control group and Steyr barrel. The 95 was originally milled to accept double stack magazines and was the only AK imported with zero US made parts. It was only imported from 1995-1998. All other Arsenal SLRs were produced in the U.S. from a satalite arsenal factory in Nevada. The Arsenal factory in nevada uses the same specs as the Bulgarian factory, and they produce some of the best AKs on the market, but they simply cannot compare to the AKs produced in the original Bulgarian factory. Simply do a little research on the web, and you'll understand why the SLR-95 is in a class of its own. You rarely see these things on armslist, and if you do, they're expensive & they go fast....why... because THEY ARE FREAKIN' BAD-ASS!!!

I've replaced the original front & rear sight with mepro-light tritium night sights, but I still have the original sights for all you pure-ist out there. I've also added a tapco T6 adjustable stock, hogue grip & aluminum front quad-rail, but again for you pure-ist I've still got the original thumbhole arsenal stock & foregrip. I'm also going to throw in 10 steel mags & 1860 rounds of 7.62x39 wolf & tulla hp & fmj.

For the right price/trade I'll even cerakote it the color or camo pattern of your choice.

For the right trade I could also throw in my trijicon reflex sight w/ quick detach ARMS mount
 (to see cerakote gallery check out www.cerakotepros.com)

I'm not really sure I wanna let this thing go, but I am curious to see whats out there. Please text me any cash or trade offers to REDACTED. the worst I can say is no thanks. Please keep in mind I know what this package is worth, and I'll only trade for something of equal value. Also, I'm willing to throw in cash for the right trade. 
Thanks & good luck!

title: For Sale:  Taurus PT 25
postcontent:
Taurus Security System (TSS)b
Taurus family of semi-auto pistols all feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with each gun). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.
